INTELLI-CREDIT
Next-Gen Corporate Credit Appraisal Engine
Deep Analysis & Detailed System Architecture
Hackathon Build Guide
This document provides a complete technical blueprint for building the Intelli-Credit AI-powered Credit
Decisioning Engine. It covers system architecture, component-by-component implementation strategy,
the recommended tech stack, and curated open-source GitHub references to accelerate development.
1. Deep Problem Analysis
What the Problem Is Really Asking
The Intelli-Credit challenge requires building a multi-agent AI pipeline that replaces a human credit manager
end-to-end. It stacks three distinct hard problems together:
# Problem Why It's Hard
1 Multi-format document intelligence Scanned Indian PDFs, GSTR reconciliation, bank statement parsing with messy layouts
2 Autonomous web research Finding litigation, MCA filings, RBI regulations, promoter news without human input
3 Explainable credit decision A transparent Word/PDF memo with reasons — not a black box ML output
India-Specific Complexity
The Indian context introduces domain-specific challenges that generic LLMs handle poorly. The following
nuances must be explicitly addressed in the solution:
GSTR-2A vs 3B Reconciliation: 2A is auto-populated purchase register; 3B is self-declared return. Mismatches
signal circular trading or input credit fraud.
CIBIL Commercial Reports: India's credit bureau format differs from Western equivalents. CMR (CIBIL MSME
Rank) and CCR (Company Credit Report) have unique fields.
MCA21 Portal: Director DIN tracking, charge satisfaction status, annual return filings — all must be scraped from
mca.gov.in.
e-Courts / NJDG: National Judicial Data Grid holds litigation records. Must search by company name AND
promoter names.
Scanned Regional PDFs: Many Indian SME documents are scanned in low DPI or contain Hindi/regional
language headers requiring OCR tuning.
