3. Component-by-Component Build Plan
Pillar 1 — Data Ingestor
Step 1: Document Classification
Use a simple classifier (or LLM prompt) to route each uploaded PDF to the right parser: Annual Report, Bank
Statement, GST Return, Legal Notice, Sanction Letter, etc. File naming + a zero-shot LLM classification prompt
is sufficient for a hackathon.
Step 2: OCR + Parsing
• Scanned PDFs: pytesseract + pdf2image, OR Azure Document Intelligence / AWS Textract for higher accuracy
on Indian scans
• Digital PDFs: pdfplumber or PyMuPDF for text extraction with layout preservation
• Tables in bank statements: camelot or tabula-py
• Multi-format enterprise option: llmware (open source, handles OCR, tables, images in one pipeline)
Step 3: LLM-Powered Structured Extraction
After OCR, chunk the text and pass it to Claude/GPT-4o with a structured extraction prompt. Request JSON
output for easy downstream processing:
Extract: Revenue, EBITDA, Total Debt, Net Worth, Director Names, Auditor Remarks, Related
Party Transactions. Return as JSON with keys: revenue, ebitda, total_debt, net_worth,
directors[], auditor_remarks, related_party_flag.
Step 4: GST vs Bank Statement Cross-Validation (Circular Trading Detection)
• Parse GSTR-3B (declared sales) vs GSTR-2A (purchase-side auto-populated register)
• Compare against bank credit entries for the same period
• Flag if bank deposits significantly exceed GST turnover — potential revenue inflation
• Flag large cash credits with no GST equivalent — potential circular trading
• Compute a GST Compliance Score (ratio of filed months to total months in period)
Pillar 2 — Research Agent (Digital Credit Manager)
Use LangGraph to orchestrate multiple specialized sub-agents running in parallel. Each agent has a specific
research mandate:
News Agent Searches for [company name] + [promoter names] + 'fraud / NPA / default / litigation' via Tavily
or SerpAPI. Runs sentiment analysis on returned articles.
MCA Agent Scrapes mca.gov.in for director DIN history, charges filed against the company, satisfaction of
charges, ROC show-cause notices.
e-Courts Agent Searches the National Judicial Data Grid (njdg.gov.in) for cases filed by or against the
company and its promoters.
Sector Agent Fetches latest RBI/SEBI/MoF circulars relevant to the company's NIC code / industry sector.
Summarizes regulatory headwinds.
Qualitative Input
Portal
A Streamlit form where the Credit Officer types notes (e.g., 'Factory at 40% capacity'). These
get embedded as high-weight nodes in the scoring pipeline.
Pillar 3 — Recommendation Engine
Feature Engineering — The 5 Cs of Credit
C Dimension Key Features
Character Trustworthiness & track recordLitigation count, promoter news sentiment score, MCA compliance, prior defaults
Capacity Ability to repay DSCR, ICR, Revenue CAGR (3yr), EBITDA margins, operating leverage
Capital Financial strength Debt/Equity ratio, Tangible Net Worth, promoter equity contribution %
Collateral Security coverage Asset Coverage Ratio, security type (immovable/movable), LTV, encumbrance
Conditions External environment Industry outlook score, regulatory risk rating, qualitative notes weight
Scoring Model — XGBoost + SHAP
XGBoost with SHAP (SHapley Additive exPlanations) is the optimal choice for this problem. SHAP values
provide per-feature contribution scores that directly satisfy the evaluation criterion on explainability. The output
can state exactly: 'Rejected due to high litigation risk (-23 pts) despite strong GST flows (+18 pts).' Include a
SHAP waterfall chart in the CAM for visual impact.
CAM Generator
Feed extracted features + SHAP scores + research findings into an LLM prompt structured around the 5 Cs
template. Use python-docx to render the final Word document with proper headings, tables, and the SHAP chart
embedded as an image. Optionally convert to PDF using LibreOffice in headless mode or WeasyPrint.
Sample CAM Decision Output: APPROVED — Rs. 5 Crore Term Loan @ 11.5% p.a. (3-year tenor) Rationale: Strong
GST-verified turnover of Rs. 28 Cr/yr (+18 pts) and clean MCA records (+12 pts) offset moderate DSCR of 1.3x (-8 pts).
Promoter news sentiment neutral. Qualitative note 'Factory at 40% capacity' applied as conditional risk flag (-5 pts).
Collateral coverage at 1.6x provides adequate buffer. Net Score: 74/100 (Threshold: 60).
